                <note rend="inline" type="source">365D.1163/128: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-11-30T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 30, 1938—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>119. General Conference of Seventh Day Adventist Church has received cable from
                    its European representative reporting that the Adventist mission properties at
                    Addis Ababa and Addis Alem have been expropriated by Italian authorities who
                    have also apparently demanded that mission hospital at Addis Ababa be turned
                    over by December 8th. Please investigate and telegraph whether report is correct
                    and what are the intentions of Italian authorities regarding the mission’s
                    activities in Ethiopia.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
